      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Describing the mindset of these attackers can be a challenging task, but framing it in a way that resonates with your staff can be helpful. You could say that these attackers are like a \"master thief\" or a \"social engineer\" who uses their skills to \"pick the lock\" on their target's defenses. \n\nThink of them as a type of \"professional trickster\" who uses their intelligence and cunning to manipulate others into divulging sensitive information. They're like a \"goblin\" who lurks in the shadows, watching and waiting for the perfect moment to strike.\n\nBy framing them in this way, you can help your staff understand that these attackers are not just malicious individuals, but rather a sophisticated and calculated threat. This can help to demystify the threat and make it more relatable, which can be an effective way to build awareness and prevent attacks.\n\nIt's also worth noting that these attackers often have a \"script\" or a \"plan\" that they follow, and they're not just winging it. They're often highly organized and methodical in their approach, which can make them even more difficult to detect.",
